This article is a transcript of President Donald Trump's remarks at The Hermitage in Nashville, Tennessee, on March 15, 2017. In his speech, Trump pays tribute to Andrew Jackson, the seventh President of the United States, on the occasion of his 250th birthday. Trump highlights Jackson's rise from poverty to greatness, his defiance of authority, and his fight against government corruption. Trump also draws parallels between himself and Jackson, emphasizing their shared goal of protecting the rights of the American people. He concludes by expressing his commitment to making America great again and honoring the legacy of Andrew Jackson.